notes: Human and mouse non-coding sequences were introduced to test for enhancer activity. Stains for gene expression.

name: Cell Cycle Jurkat Cells
notes: According to authors, fluorescent markers might affect the biological process under study, so their model is trained without fluorescence. Images are captured via imaging flow cytometry.

name: Human U2OS cells (out of focus)
notes: Task is to segment nuclei (count cells), given in focus and out of focus images.

name: Human U2OS cells – RNAi Cell Painting experiment
notes: Experiment attempted to induce gene knockdown via 315 unique RNAi. Components are from channel.

name: Nuclei of U2OS cells in a chemical screen
notes: Chemical screen was performed. However, labels are not available for phenotype.

name: Human U2OS cells cytoplasm–nucleus translocation
notes: Excluded channel (FKHR-EGFP) which is localized in nucleus or cytoplasm. Inhibition of nuclear export by two compounds leads to accumulation of FKHR-EGFP in the nucleus.

name: Human U2OS cells cytoplasm–nucleus translocation (2)
notes: Excluded channel of transcription factor NFKB. Localization in the nucleus or cytoplasm is tested against varying concentration of TNFa.

name: Human U2OS cells transfluor
notes: 2nd channel is GFP-stained arrestin, which may be in the cytoplasm. Beta adrenergic receptor modification causes vesicle-like spots in the cytoplasm when stimulated.

name: Synthetic cells
notes: Filename nomenclature `SIMCEPImages_well_Ccells_Fblur;_ssamples_wstain.TIF`; intensity of focus blur applied ranges from 1 (no blur) to 48. 'F1' in filename is for fully focused/ground-truth images. Nucleus counts are also given.

name: Human kidney cortex cells
notes: 3D Images (7 z-slices per image). Original task is to classify cell type based on 3D nuclei staining.

name: Human HT29 colon-cancer cells shRNAi screen
notes: 4903 shRNAi screens were done to find regulators of mitosis. Roughly 4331 images have 1+ classes: protein/mechanism of action (?)

name: Human Hepatocyte and Murine Fibroblast cells – Co-culture experiment
notes: Human hepatocyte and murine fibroblasts are co-cultured. Both can be seen within an image.

name: Human MCF7 cells – compound-profiling experiment

name: P. vivax (malaria) infected human blood smears

name: Drosophila Kc167 cells (2)
notes: Number of cells per image is given. Images come from 10 fields per 5 samples (1 wildtype, 4 RNAi gene knockdowns).

name: C. elegans metabolism assay

name: C. elegans infection marker
